### Code Quality Standards
- Follow PEP 8 for Python, ESLint/Prettier for JavaScript
- Use type hints in Python, PropTypes/TypeScript in React
- Write comprehensive tests with 80%+ coverage
- Implement proper error handling and validation
- Use semantic HTML and ensure accessibility compliance

### Security First
- Validate all inputs on client and server
- Use Django's security features (CSRF, XSS protection)
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Sanitize user inputs and use parameterized queries
- Follow HTTPS and secure headers in all environments

### Performance Optimization
- Use database indexes and query optimization
- Implement caching with Redis for frequently accessed data
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Implement code splitting and lazy loading
- Optimize images and assets for web delivery